Description:
Looking to Invest ? Solid older style apartment in convenient location.
This first floor apartment is currently leased for 12 months at $300 per week. Have the tenants enjoy the convenience of Batman Station, Bunnings, Coles, Sydney Road, trams and the CBD.
• First floor, with front balcony accessed from living area.
• Glowing timber blue gum parquetry floors, on sound proof underlay, accentuates the open design .
• Flow on style using a timber breakfast bar and matching stools.
• Elegant look all white new kitchen cabinets with Swedish designed soft close hinges and pantry with stainless steel slide out drawers.
• Built-in desk, study or computer area. Sound treatment to adjoining party wall.
• As new electric cooker and range hood. New circuit board.
• Separate bathroom with shower over bath and under bench laundry facilities.
• Single carport and storage shed.
• Block of only 7 apartments.
Build your wealth with property!!
Inspect by appointment or as advertised.
Agent in Conjunction McLeod Real Estate & Finance Cath McLeod 0412352338

Description:
Live It Up
In a secure and elegantly landscaped complex this three bedroom residence invites you upstairs to live it up on a private paved entertainer's terrace. Just a stroll to a wide range of amenities, the home opens into a spacious living, meals and kitchen featuring polished floorboards, a breakfast bar and stainless steel appliances including a gas cooktop and fan forced oven. The first of three double bedrooms is found on the ground floor, while two upstairs bedrooms host mirrored built-in robes. There's both a shower and separate bath in the bathroom, plus a laundry and second toilet on the floor below. A retractable awning makes the terrace inviting in different seasons and extra features of the home include heating, cooling, an intercom and secure parking space. Cafes, various modes of transport, Lake Reserve, schools and Coburg Market in vibrant Sydney Road are all just a stroll, and local favourite O'Heas Bakery is also nearby.

Description:
Captivating Bungalow Dressed To Impress!
Beautifully renovated and extended Californian Bungalow with multiple living zones, four spacious bedrooms, oozing period detail throughout will thrill large families that want it all. Summer days can be spent lounging around the pool whilst entertaining friends and family under the covered alfresco area. For those that work from home there is a private, self- contained studio off the garage, abundant storage and of course outdoor shower and w/c. Large 634m2 allotment and wide side drive to double garage offers easy off street parking.
Accommodation includes:
• Welcoming formal entrance hallway
• Master bedroom with BIR's and full ensuite bathroom
• Spacious 2nd bedroom with BIR's
• Formal lounge room with OFP
• Central bathroom with freestanding claw bath and shower
• Separate w/c
• 3rd bedroom with BIR's
• Huge 2nd level 4th bedroom with pool views
• Massive living /meals area opening to covered, heated alfresco(overlooking rear yard)
• Adjoining fully equipped kitchen with two pantries, heaps of bench and cupboard space
Featuring: lead lighting, polished Baltic pine floorboards, quality window furnishings, gas ducted heating, multiple split systems, salt water chlorinated pool with solar heating and pool equipment, remote garage and gate, security alarm system.
This wonderful family home has everything you could ever need to entertain, live comfortably and enjoy easy access to transport, schools, shopping , Citylink and Tullamarine Freeways.

Description:
Low-Maintenance Lifestyle In Dream Location
Presenting city fringe living at its best with this two bedroom brick villa unit situated in a highly sought-after, prestigious pocket of Coburg moments to Sydney Road and Nicholson Street, trams, trains, restaurants, shops and Merri Creek parklands. Behinds its 70's exterior, this on-trend pad possesses understated elegance, with polished floorboards and sympathetically re-vamped wet areas. Swish living zones include a timber-on-white kitchen featuring 600mm S/S Smeg oven, and S/S double-drawer dishwasher. Ample accommodation provided with two double-sized bedrooms (BIR's) and tastefully updated bathroom with wave vanity and frameless glass bath/shower. With a serene private north facing courtyard at its inner sanctum - complemented by a second rear courtyard - this is a special find, set to embrace every modern lifestyle. Includes OSP, internal laundry, heating/cooling.

Description:
Timeless perfection on a 589m2 corner block
Beyond a classic façade lies a graceful three bedroom two bathroom home whose period perfect interiors are flawlessly presented. Resplendent with soaring ornate ceilings, open fireplaces and leadlight details it offers an outstanding lifestyle or development potential (STCA), moments to schools, transport and culinary delights of Sydney Road. Priced to Sell - Fully Furnished
Located in a highly sought-after pocket of Coburg within close proximity to all local amenities making it the right choice for your new home or investment.

Description:
AUCTION this Saturday 27/10 at 1pm
Step up and take this 'picture perfect' California Bungalow on approximately 523 m2 into the future. High ceilings and polished floorboards work with a flexible floor plan currently flaunting a large living room with open fireplace, kitchen/meals adjoining a dining zone and two double bedrooms, sharing a central bathroom. Situated in a peaceful street, this home has abundant scope for savvy enhancements utilising its beautiful façade and generous land size. In one of Coburg's best positions, it is only moments to Moreland Train Station, John Fawkner Hospital, Coburg West Primary & The Sydney Rd Shopping/Café Precinct.

Description:
Edwardian Elegance with Gorgeous Garden Surrounds
Beyond the captivating facade of this distinctive period home, discover a warm and inviting interior that delivers an inner-urban lifestyle of quality and convenience along with plenty of room to further expand in the future (STCA). With towering ceilings and an abundance of natural light throughout, the home's impressive interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms, updated bathroom and separate WC. Add to this a spacious lounge/dining area and stylish timber-bench kitchen with pressed-metal splashbacks and Asko/Ilve appliances. Other features include hydronic heating, solar power, plantation shutters and solid timber floors, open fireplaces, internal laundry, plus a surprisingly deep backyard with brick-paved undercover patio, lush gardens, huge watertank as well as the added advantage of two-car front off-street parking. Walking distance to Batman Station, O'Hea Street buses and Sydney Road trams, it's also close to primary and secondary schools, Coburg Lake, local cafes and Coburg's renowned shopping precinct. Land 12.19m x 39.62m (483 sqm) approx.
Insights: 38 May Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Positioned just a short stroll from Sydney Road shops, cafes and trams, this single level villa in a boutique development (one of only 5) boasts a broad appeal that will attract first home buyers, professional couples, astute investors and those looking to scale down. The comfortable interior presents ample scope to add your personal touch and comprises 2 bedrooms (one with BIRs), spacious living and dining, separate kitchen with direct access to the private courtyard, central bathroom with laundry facilities and air-conditioning. All About Relaxed Living
Nestled in a tree lined street surrounded by its peers, this inviting three bedroom plus study Californian Bungalow is all about relaxed living. Behind a picket fence lies a substantial home where lofty ceilings, fretwork and leadlight detail add charisma to a free flowing floorplan that features a generous lounge with etched glass doors, flowing to a bright kitchen/meals whose traditional layout includes gas upright cooking and a dishwasher. Description:
Boutique Luxury with Amazing Space
Set well back from the street in an exclusive complex of only six, this three-level townhouse presents an outstanding inner-urban lifestyle with its oversized interior, premium features throughout and idyllic Brunswick-edge location. Beautifully-appointed interior showcases three main bedrooms (large master with WIR and ensuite), study/fourth bedroom, stylish central bathroom and additional powder room (third WC). Add to this a superb stone-bench kitchen with soft-close cabinetry and all-Bosch appliances, expansive open-plan living/dining area with stacker doors revealing a full-width undercover entertaining terrace complete black-mesh cafe blind for added privacy. Other stand-out features include split-system heating and cooling (all levels), quality carpets and solid hardwood floors, LED lighting throughout, NBN connection, video intercom, European laundry and excellent storage spaces plus an internally-accessed two-car garage. The convenience of city-bound trams virtually at your doorstep, it's also close to popular cafes and local shops, as well as a range of schools, extensive parkland and endless Merri Creek trails. Modern lifestyle perfection!

Description:
Brimming With Light and Charisma
A charismatic renovation of this classic two bedroom plus study Bungalow delivers a modern minimalism allowing glistening leadlight windows, plate rails and polished Baltic Pine floors to shine through its expansive interiors. Brimming with light, this brightly renovated home presenting a picture perfect facade, boasts the lofty ceilings and grand proportions of its period pedigree. Showcasing a wide entrance hall, this home features charming lounge and dining, both with original fireplaces and separated by etched glass doors offering versatility and privacy through the generous living domain. A bright kitchen with breakfast nook boasts pressed metal ceilings and enjoys views over the expansive rear garden offering alfresco entertaining and plenty of space for children to play. Gracious bedrooms, the elegant master boasting leadlight windows, open fireplace and built-in robes share a pristine family bathroom that together with gas heaters and ample off street parking offer comfort and convenience. All in a prized south of Bell Street location boasting easy access to both Sydney Road and Melville Road shopping and trams, local cafes, Coburg Farmer's Market, O'Heas Bakery and quality schools including St Fideles Primary.

Description:
HUGE Apartment over 55sqm plus balcony!
This ultra clean modern 1 bedroom apartment is definitely one to consider as an excellent entry level into the market for first home buyers or for astute investors.
Featuring a large master bedroom with built-in-robe and access to balcony. Internal separate laundry with plenty of cupboard space, modern kitchen with Cook-Top, Stainless Steel Oven/Griller, Dishwasher and Rangehood.
Handy to Sydney Road Cafes, shops and transport!
Viewings are by appointment, Enquire Now!
NB. Regarding indicated price - Please understand that, even in a stable market, there is often more than one buyer interested in the same property. When that happens, all buyers will be given EQUAL OPPORTUNITY TO MAKE THEIR BEST OFFERS.

Description:
Delightful downsizer, first home or savvy investment
With stylish renovations, generous proportions and private wraparound alfresco courtyard, this delightful two bedroom property is a real surprise package. Tucked away to the rear, in a neat block of only four, the single level home ensures appeal for downsizers, market entrants and investors alike. Recent upgrades include double-glazed tilt and turn doors and windows throughout light filled open living/meals spaces and oversized bedrooms, with built-in-robes. Classic black and white finishes, along with s/steel appliances, modern benches, cabinetry and vanity, complement well-planned kitchen and bathroom/laundry zones. Extras include split-system, modern blinds, polished floorboards, garden sheds and carport. Walking distance from Sydney Road cafes, shops, trams and Coburg station.
Insights: 3/2 Vincent Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 73 other 2 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Period charm and contemporary class on the Avenue
In one of Coburg's best streets is this freestanding single fronted brick home showcasing two double bedrooms and north facing living/entertaining zones. Designed with impeccable attention to detail, a deceptively spacious floor plan, comprising charming living area, central dining room and well appointed kitchen with great storage and dishwasher, features leadlight aspects, soaring ceilings and decorative fireplace with cast iron insert. Robed bedrooms are elegantly served by updated bathroom/laundry with stone vanity and rain-head shower. Complemented by private all-weather alfresco, landscaped gardens, ducted heating, evaporative cooling and coveted off street parking via ROW. Stroll to vibrant cafe, shopping strips, city transport, schools and parklands.
Insights: 43 The Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Period Charmer In Prime Location
Centrally located just walking distance to Coburg North Village, Batman station, Coburg North Primary School and Harmony Park, this three bedroom home invites families, couples and investors to enjoy the easy going lifestyle on offer. Set upon a pristinely landscaped block presenting picturesque front and rear gardens, a handsome façade boasts leadlight windows and clinker brick portico entry. The interior is framed by high decorative ceilings within a floor plan comprising spacious open living area with OFP and fully appointed timber kitchen. A pergola covers the large entertaining area while well scaled bedrooms include generous BIRs. Serviced by a central spa bathroom, laundry and second toilet, there's also split system air conditioning, ducted heating, water tank, driveway and a garage.
Insights: 35 Kerferd Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.
